eNCA's Lindokuhle Xulu has the details. #eNCA #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Some Soweto residents say outages in their area are not related to rolling blackouts. Soweto residents are planning to protest at Eskom's Megawatt Park Head Office. They're unhappy with constant power cuts which they say are not related to the rolling power outages. eNCA's Lindokuhle Xulu is on this story. Courtesy #DStv403 On Wednesday, they protested at Eskom's Megawatt Park as the power utility continues to implement higher stages of power cuts. Eskom implemented Stage 4 power cuts from 2pm until 10pm on Wednesday. The power utility says the blackouts are necessary after the loss of generation units at the Kusile and other power stations. Eskom says the probability of further power cuts remains high and they have urged all South Africans to reduce their use of electricity. Watch the videos above for more details.